item.title: Economic reform, global action after virus
item.description: Scott Morrison is turning his mind to economic reform and overhauling global bodies as Australia's coronavirus infection rate plummets.

item.title: March retail surges 8.2% amid stockpiling
item.description: Retail turnover surged by a monthly record of 8.2 per cent in March as consumers stockpiled groceries and office supplies in anticipation of coronavirus lockdown measures

item.title: COVID-19 hits 130,000 jobs in Qld
item.description: About 130,000 Queenslanders have lost their jobs or had their hours drastically cut through forced business closures, treasury officials estimate.

item.title: Welfare job-hunting activity still on hold
item.description: Welfare recipients will not need to look for work for at least another month due to the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Trump immigration ban to last 60 days
item.description: President Donald Trump says his new immigration ban will last for 60 days and apply to those seeking "green cards" for permanent residency in an effort to protect Americans seeking to regain jobs lost because of the coronavirus.

item.title: SA Pathology to remain in public hands
item.description: The improved performance and commitment to quality care and sustainability has enabled SA Pathology to be spared from privatisation.

item.title: Bondi Beach to re-open only for exercise
item.description: Sydney's iconic Bondi Beach will partially open to swimmers and surfers next week as more beaches in NSW begin easing COVID-19 restrictions.

item.title: Anzac meaning renewed amid virus: Premier
item.description: The sacrifices of earlier generations will be more significant than ever this Anzac Day, NSW Premier Gladys Berejiklian says, as the state's residents prepare to commemorate from their homes amid the fight against COVID-19.

item.title: WA man charged over child sex abuse videos
item.description: A West Australian man has been accused of using an encrypted online messaging forum to share abhorrent videos of children being sexually abused and tortured.

item.title: NSW virus toll hits 33, teachers slam plan
item.description: The NSW coronavirus toll has hit 33 after three people died over the past 24 hours, including a third person from a virus-hit western Sydney nursing home.
